<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.10.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#354">Justice</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.10.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80196" speakername="Tricia Marwick (Mid Scotland and Fife) (SNP)" spid="S1W-354" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#354">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive what is the estimated cost to the voluntary sector in Scotland of criminal record checks on volunteers who work with children and young people.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.10.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80252" speakername="Mr Jim Wallace" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#354">

  <p>Part V of the Police Act 1997 provides for extended access to criminal record checks and planning for implementation is currently underway. At this stage it is too early to estimate the cost to the voluntary sector and we are keeping the matter under review as the project progresses. The checks are not mandatory and it will be for voluntary organisations to decide when a check is required and whether to re-imburse the individual.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.11.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#320">Social Security</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.11.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80220" speakername="Alex Neil (Central Scotland) (SNP)" spid="S1W-320" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#320">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether there will be a Concordat with Her Majesty&#146;s Government covering Housing Benefits and other Social Security matters and, if so, when the draft concordat will be published and submitted to the Parliament.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.11.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80131" speakername="Ms Wendy Alexander" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#320">

  <p>Draft concordats have yet to be received from the UK Government. Once they have been considered by the Executive and agreed with the UK Government, they will be presented to the Scottish Parliament for its endorsement before they come into effect.</p>

</reply>


<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.12.h" nospeaker="True" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#438">Tourism</minor-heading>

<ques id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.12.q0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80142" speakername="Bruce Crawford (Mid Scotland and Fife) (SNP)" spid="S1W-438" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#438">

  <p>To ask the Scottish Executive whether, in the light of the review of the funding of area tourist boards announced by the Deputy Minister for Highland and Islands and Gaelic on 24 June 1999, it will provide details of the review&#146;s remit, who will be involved in the review process and when the outcome will be published.</p>

</ques>


<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/spwa/1999-07-20.12.r0" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/member/80214" speakername="Mr Alasdair Morrison" url="http://www.scottish.parliament.uk/business/pqa/wa-99/wa0720.htm#438">

  <p>I intend to write to all those who have an interest in how Area Tourist Boards are funded seeking their views. I will place a copy of our consultation letter in the Parliament&#146;s library.</p>

</reply>
</publicwhip>